            "answer_text": "Benazir's wedding was purely for political connections at that time. PPP at that time had strength in both Punjab and Sindh but no stronghold. There were names like Faisal Saleh Hayat, a Punjabi, that were considered to have a hold in Punjab but eventually it was decided that Hakim Ali Zardari's son be wed to Benazir to have a political stronghold in Sindh. That decision shows till day when we see Pakistan Peoples Party still reigning without a strong opponent in Sindh province. ",
